What I find funny about this is that I never thought it was terrible that low level melee-class people had to use other players to get a bind. My issue has always been that it's just incredibly demeaning and disrespectful to make higher level melee's run around begging...<br>
<br>
Why does it have to be all or nothing with Verant?<br>
<br>
It seems to me that the Soulbinders shouldn't talk/deal with all players until they reach a certain minimal level (anywhere from 20-35, personally I would say 35) and then only at a substantial cost... This cost could decrease until one hit 50 whereas they would just bind you for free out of courtesy...<br>
<br>
Or am I just weird? <p><BR>
